# Code Quality Assessment: MiniML Compiler

## Overall Impression

This is a capable, feature-rich compiler supporting HM type inference, row-polymorphic
records/effects/variants, GADTs, typeclasses with fundeps, algebraic effects, and three
backends. The architecture is sound -- clean pipeline from lexing through parsing,
typechecking, and code generation with good separation between surface and typed ASTs.
The code works and passes a large test suite.

That said, several recurring patterns prevent it from reaching "professional-grade" quality.
Findings are organized by severity.

---

## 1. Systemic Code Duplication (Most Impactful Issue)

### Typechecker: Type annotation resolution (~500 lines, 8 copies)

> **Status: Mostly done.** Consolidated into `resolve_ty_annot_shared` and
> `resolve_ty_annot_def` with `make_def_resolve_var` factory. 3 of the original 8 copies
> (`resolve_field`, `resolve_alias`, `resolve_nt`) no longer exist. Two local resolvers
> remain: `process_class_def`'s local `resolve` and `resolve_inst_tys`'s local `go`, which
> have slightly different TGen/TVar strategies that could still be unified.

### Typechecker: Typed AST tree walkers (~400 lines, 7+ copies)

> **Status: Mostly done.** Generic `iter_texpr_children` and `map_texpr_children` helpers
> exist and are used by `find_var_type_in`, `strip_tail_resume`, `classify_texpr`. 6 manual
> walkers remain but 4 are intentionally selective (handler analysis functions that only
> check specific control flow patterns), and 1 uses the generic helper as fallback. The
> remaining manual walker in `infer_implicit_constraints` has complex enough logic to
> justify explicit matching.

### Native codegen: Save/restore context (~200 lines, ~15 copies)

> **Status: Mostly done.** `with_fresh_ir` helper exists and is used at 16 call sites.
> 3 manual sites remain: 2 are error-recovery rollbacks in module/stdlib compilation that
> restore broader state (global_decls, string_globals, buffer positions, hashtable
> snapshots) beyond what `with_fresh_ir` handles; 1 partial site only restores `ctx.ir`.

### Parser: Type parameter + deriving clause parsing (~120 lines, 3x each)

> **Status: Mostly done.** Shared `parse_type_params_decl` and `parse_deriving` helpers
> exist and are reused across all three sites. The type definition body parsing
> (record/variant/alias) is still duplicated between main and `and` clauses (~24 lines).

### Types.ml: `generalize`/`generalize_with_map` and `instantiate`/`instantiate_with_mapping`

Each pair is ~150 lines of near-identical code differing only in whether the ID map is
returned.

